with numerous short, erect hairs, especially laterally; rather dense, short, recumbent on remaining tergites; bullae (Fig. 54) about three times as long as broad. Sternites with sparse and recumbent hairs, more numerous on 6-8; 0' 8 about one-third lenght of 7. Females with sparse and reci mbent hairs on segments 2-7, numerous erect to slightly retrorse hairs on 8 and a few on 9; tergite 9 fluted and one and one-half times as wide at the apex as at the base; apex with short hairs (Fig. 61). Some species with fine punctures on segments 2-8 and female segment 8 shallowly rugose. Male genitalia (Figs. 122-124): hypandrium completely coalesced with basistyli, resulting structure subquadrate; apical processes of gonopods subrectangular, their apical margin straight; superomedian part of the fused gonopods projected ventrally; aedeagus a conical tube, with lateral apodemes dorsally bent, pointed; epandrial halves and cerci coalescent for a short distance at base; epandrial halves wide, bent in their apical margin, bent part fused to epandrial wall.
